WEBVTT

1
00:00:57.872 --> 00:01:02.872
Subtitles by explosiveskull + Corrected offset with https://subshifter.bitsnbites.eu/
www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:01:21.506 --> 00:01:22.967
Captain. where are you?

3
00:01:23.425 --> 00:01:25.469
I'm heading there with my sister's family.

4
00:01:26.011 --> 00:01:27.679
We're almost there. so hang on.

5
00:01:32.017 --> 00:01:33.602
Is this the right way?

6
00:01:33.894 --> 00:01:35.729
I drove through here dozens of times.

7
00:01:36.396 --> 00:01:38.232
All the other roads would be packed with cars.

8
00:01:45.614 --> 00:01:46.740
Oh...

9
00:01:49.952 --> 00:01:52.329
Please give us a ride.

10
00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:56.166
I have a little girl. I have a wife too.

11
00:01:56.791 --> 00:01:58.752
Please take us to the port.

12
00:02:00.295 --> 00:02:01.630
I'm begging you...

13
00:02:01.713 --> 00:02:04.133
I wasn't bitten! It's not a bite!

14
00:02:09.263 --> 00:02:12.807
If we look dangerous.
at least take our girl. Please.

15
00:02:12.892 --> 00:02:14.434
Sir?

16
00:02:15.144 --> 00:02:17.354
Please! I'm begging you!

17
00:02:18.105 --> 00:02:19.273
Sir! Please!

18
00:02:22.692 --> 00:02:23.861
Jung-seok...

19
00:02:25.404 --> 00:02:26.989
Don't say anything until we're on the ship!

20
00:02:34.496 --> 00:02:37.791
Can you tell us
why this dreadful virus has spread. Paul?

21
00:02:38.208 --> 00:02:40.627
Well. unfortunately. we don't have much information

22
00:02:40.835 --> 00:02:44.256
other than the fact that it started
out of a bio-factory in South Korea.

23
00:02:44.339 --> 00:02:49.053
Uh. it's unclear exactly
how this unidentified virus initially began to spread.

24
00:02:49.636 --> 00:02:52.890
Of course.
sheer pandemonium broke loose in South Korea.

25
00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:55.475
And many people began to believe a rumor

26
00:02:55.559 --> 00:02:56.894
that was circulating online

27
00:02:56.977 --> 00:02:59.229
{\an8}about a safe region somewhere further down south...

28
00:02:59.313 --> 00:03:01.731
{\an8}Busan? Is this the correct pronunciation?

29
00:03:01.815 --> 00:03:04.068
{\an8}That's right. People were evacuated there.

30
00:03:04.151 --> 00:03:06.904
{\an8}But in the end. no place was truly safe.

31
00:03:06.987 --> 00:03:10.699
{\an8}But there is an absolute safe place
on the Korean Peninsula.

32
00:03:10.782 --> 00:03:13.743
That's correct.
I believe you're referring to North Korea.

33
00:03:14.328 --> 00:03:17.581
Perhaps it's fortunate
that this happened before the reunification!

34
00:03:17.664 --> 00:03:18.916
So it turns out.

35
00:03:19.249 --> 00:03:22.878
So how long before the Korean government
lost all control?

36
00:03:22.962 --> 00:03:24.504
Just one day.

37
00:03:26.798 --> 00:03:29.176
Please move slowly!

38
00:03:29.676 --> 00:03:31.511
This is Alpha One.

39
00:03:32.679 --> 00:03:33.680
Move on!

40
00:03:33.763 --> 00:03:34.764
Be careful!

41
00:03:48.737 --> 00:03:49.779
This is Alpha Two.

42
00:03:49.864 --> 00:03:51.698
We have about 50 civilians waiting for boarding.

43
00:04:07.882 --> 00:04:08.966
Uncle.

44
00:04:12.677 --> 00:04:13.888
Are you all right. Dong-hwan?

45
00:04:14.304 --> 00:04:15.305
Yes.

46
00:04:15.973 --> 00:04:16.974
Where's Chul-min?

47
00:04:17.391 --> 00:04:19.309
He went to get some relief aid.

48
00:04:20.268 --> 00:04:24.398
But shouldn't we have arrived in Japan by now?

49
00:04:25.357 --> 00:04:27.526
I'm sure we're almost there. don't worry.

50
00:04:29.069 --> 00:04:30.070
Captain!

51
00:04:33.823 --> 00:04:34.824
What is it?

52
00:04:34.909 --> 00:04:36.869
We're being rerouted to Hong Kong.

53
00:04:38.203 --> 00:04:39.204
Why all of sudden?

54
00:04:39.538 --> 00:04:41.040
They're not telling me why.

55
00:04:43.417 --> 00:04:44.793
I have to go check something.

56
00:04:57.932 --> 00:04:59.058
Excuse me.

57
00:05:01.226 --> 00:05:03.312
I'll ask about it.
so go and check what's going on.

58
00:05:03.395 --> 00:05:04.396
Yes. sir.

59
00:05:05.022 --> 00:05:06.065
Excuse me.

60
00:05:06.481 --> 00:05:07.482
Excuse me.

61
00:05:14.198 --> 00:05:15.199
Uh.

62
00:05:44.269 --> 00:05:45.312
Sir!

63
00:05:46.688 --> 00:05:47.689
Sir!

64
00:05:47.982 --> 00:05:50.109
Is it true that we are rerouting to Hong Kong?

65
00:05:50.192 --> 00:05:51.986
Please return to your seats.

66
00:05:52.486 --> 00:05:54.571
We need to understand the situation. sir!

67
00:05:55.447 --> 00:05:56.949
Everyone's getting nervous.

68
00:05:57.241 --> 00:06:00.619
Please return to your seat
and await further instructions.

69
00:06:00.702 --> 00:06:01.745
Sir!

70
00:06:01.871 --> 00:06:02.872
We have a problem.

71
00:06:02.955 --> 00:06:05.249
We've found an infected person
on the lower deck cabins.

72
00:06:06.833 --> 00:06:07.834
We get ramen too?

73
00:06:10.379 --> 00:06:12.089
Come in. Leave your bag here.

74
00:06:12.172 --> 00:06:13.173
It looks good.

75
00:06:13.340 --> 00:06:14.341
Please come in.

76
00:06:14.799 --> 00:06:16.135
- Infected!
- What?

77
00:06:20.805 --> 00:06:21.849
What is it?

78
00:07:17.321 --> 00:07:19.073
It's okay. I'll be right here.

79
00:07:19.573 --> 00:07:22.993
Breathe. Dong-hwan. I'm not going anywhere.

80
00:07:23.493 --> 00:07:24.661
It'll be okay.

81
00:07:24.912 --> 00:07:26.746
Look at me.

82
00:07:30.500 --> 00:07:33.628
I'll be right here with you.

83
00:07:37.716 --> 00:07:40.177
What do I do?

84
00:07:41.929 --> 00:07:44.348
Your uncle's here. Dong-hwan.

85
00:07:48.727 --> 00:07:49.728
Sis...

86
00:07:50.145 --> 00:07:52.106
- What do we do?
- We have to go.

87
00:07:52.189 --> 00:07:53.523
We have to go now. come on!

88
00:07:55.067 --> 00:07:56.861
- Let's go!
- Your uncle...

89
00:07:58.653 --> 00:07:59.696
We have to go!

90
00:08:00.990 --> 00:08:02.116
We must leave.

91
00:08:02.199 --> 00:08:03.200
Come on!

92
00:08:05.035 --> 00:08:06.078
Sis!

93
00:08:23.595 --> 00:08:25.805
Sis! Sis!

94
00:08:40.319 --> 00:08:41.363
Honey!

95
00:08:42.696 --> 00:08:43.697
No!

96
00:09:18.483 --> 00:09:20.986
There is even a case of infected hosts

97
00:09:21.070 --> 00:09:23.948
that were found on the last lifeboats
to leave for Hong Kong.

98
00:09:24.031 --> 00:09:25.699
After that. the neighboring countries

99
00:09:25.782 --> 00:09:28.953
decided to no longer accept any more refugees.

100
00:09:29.036 --> 00:09:31.746
In effect. Korea became completely quarantined.

101
00:09:32.164 --> 00:09:34.041
Yes. it's been four years already.

102
00:09:34.124 --> 00:09:35.834
Yes. Four years.

103
00:10:42.776 --> 00:10:43.986
Wake him up.

104
00:10:48.532 --> 00:10:50.993
Hey! Wake up!

105
00:10:55.455 --> 00:10:56.498
That's enough!

106
00:10:59.877 --> 00:11:01.420
We are not here to fight.

107
00:11:01.836 --> 00:11:03.255
The boss wants to see you.

108
00:11:06.425 --> 00:11:07.467
Hey!

109
00:11:42.377 --> 00:11:43.378
Come on.

110
00:11:51.595 --> 00:11:52.847
What are you doing here?

111
00:11:53.097 --> 00:11:54.098
Let's leave.

112
00:11:54.181 --> 00:11:55.182
Let go of me.

113
00:11:55.850 --> 00:11:56.851
Hyung!

114
00:11:56.976 --> 00:11:57.977
"Hyung."

115
00:12:00.020 --> 00:12:01.563
It means "brother." doesn't it?

116
00:12:01.771 --> 00:12:03.148
You two brothers? Huh?

117
00:12:03.398 --> 00:12:04.566
No. no. no.

118
00:12:04.649 --> 00:12:06.861
He is my dead wife's brother.

119
00:12:07.236 --> 00:12:08.445
Not brother.

120
00:12:09.446 --> 00:12:11.448
That sounds like a real tragic story.

121
00:12:13.492 --> 00:12:14.534
Have a seat.

122
00:12:15.119 --> 00:12:16.745
I don't know what the hell is it
with you people from the peninsula?

123
00:12:16.828 --> 00:12:20.374
You. uh... have an air about you.

124
00:12:20.958 --> 00:12:23.210
You have a lot of sad. sad tales...

125
00:12:23.668 --> 00:12:25.629
Let's get down to business.

126
00:12:26.088 --> 00:12:28.966
Should I say "your country"
or "the peninsula"?

127
00:12:29.549 --> 00:12:31.593
Look. I. I heard a rumor...

128
00:12:32.052 --> 00:12:35.472
There seems to be some people
that are going back down

129
00:12:35.555 --> 00:12:38.851
into the peninsula
to make their own fate.

130
00:12:39.684 --> 00:12:42.938
Zombies don't give a damn about all
that gold and money.

131
00:12:43.022 --> 00:12:45.815
which is just laying around there unguarded.

132
00:12:46.775 --> 00:12:48.318
I think it's ingenious.

133
00:12:48.402 --> 00:12:49.444
Wow.

134
00:12:50.820 --> 00:12:52.239
You want us to go back in there?

135
00:12:53.323 --> 00:12:54.824
Have you lost your mind?

136
00:12:55.534 --> 00:12:56.743
My brother.

137
00:12:57.494 --> 00:13:00.539
my mind is completely sound. thank you.

138
00:13:00.830 --> 00:13:01.831
Okay.

139
00:13:02.416 --> 00:13:03.458
So...

140
00:13:04.418 --> 00:13:06.836
the neighboring countries around the peninsula

141
00:13:06.921 --> 00:13:10.090
are controlling every ship
and plane that crosses the border.

142
00:13:11.133 --> 00:13:13.135
How would you get in or out?

143
00:13:14.261 --> 00:13:15.512
It's been done.

144
00:13:15.971 --> 00:13:18.307
You don't need to worry about the coast guard.

145
00:13:19.058 --> 00:13:20.767
As long as we keep paying them.

146
00:13:20.851 --> 00:13:23.145
the ships go in. the ships go out.

147
00:13:23.728 --> 00:13:27.274
As a matter of fact. technically.
we had the money and the truck.

148
00:13:27.900 --> 00:13:29.651
Twenty million dollars.

149
00:13:29.734 --> 00:13:31.320
Until we went missing halfway here.

150
00:13:31.403 --> 00:13:32.654
Where was the last time we...

151
00:13:32.737 --> 00:13:33.989
On the Omok Bridge.

152
00:13:34.114 --> 00:13:35.115
Mok-dong?

153
00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:37.201
What?

154
00:13:37.284 --> 00:13:38.743
Look. I don't think it's too difficult.

155
00:13:38.827 --> 00:13:40.412
You just go in at night.

156
00:13:40.495 --> 00:13:42.915
you get the truck. come back with the money.

157
00:13:42.998 --> 00:13:45.625
and don't worry about those zombies.

158
00:13:45.709 --> 00:13:48.378
I hear they are practically blind at night.

159
00:13:48.921 --> 00:13:50.005
So...

160
00:13:51.048 --> 00:13:52.967
How much money we get?

161
00:13:53.217 --> 00:13:54.218
Yeah. yeah. yeah.

162
00:13:55.886 --> 00:13:57.847
Well. that's the question. isn't it?

163
00:13:58.263 --> 00:13:59.264
Half.

164
00:14:00.432 --> 00:14:03.227
That is. if you come back alive.

165
00:14:04.103 --> 00:14:08.023
That's 2.5 million dollars per head.

166
00:14:09.024 --> 00:14:10.234
Now listen to me.

167
00:14:10.400 --> 00:14:13.195
You have no idea when or even

168
00:14:13.403 --> 00:14:18.492
if the government is ever going
to grant you any refugee status.

169
00:14:18.575 --> 00:14:21.871
so you might as well make your own goddamn future.

170
00:14:21.954 --> 00:14:22.955
Think!

171
00:14:34.424 --> 00:14:38.553
We just have to hop on a boat.
and bring the truck back.

172
00:14:38.637 --> 00:14:39.972
What's so hard about that?

173
00:14:40.430 --> 00:14:42.057
It'll only take half a day.

174
00:14:46.896 --> 00:14:49.523
Are you nuts? You want to go back there?

175
00:14:52.985 --> 00:14:55.404
Then do you want to keep living here.
getting treated like scum?

176
00:14:59.950 --> 00:15:03.037
You should have let me die
with my son and wife!

177
00:15:03.537 --> 00:15:04.704
Why did you do it?

178
00:15:05.705 --> 00:15:09.293
Had I let you die. everyone on
that ship would've died.

179
00:15:09.376 --> 00:15:10.377
Am I wrong?

180
00:15:12.629 --> 00:15:14.048
It was a sensible decision.

181
00:15:15.925 --> 00:15:17.717
Sensible decision. my ass.

182
00:15:19.469 --> 00:15:20.720
Did you even try?

183
00:15:23.348 --> 00:15:24.391
Jung-seok...

184
00:15:25.809 --> 00:15:27.477
You're tormented too!

185
00:15:29.396 --> 00:15:31.106
You just gave up!

186
00:15:35.569 --> 00:15:38.155
Whatever. forget it.

187
00:15:38.488 --> 00:15:39.489
Okay.

188
00:15:40.449 --> 00:15:43.368
Well. I'm going to go there.

189
00:15:43.452 --> 00:15:46.956
so you can do whatever you want.

190
00:15:47.706 --> 00:15:50.125
Let's just not bump into each other.

191
00:15:50.960 --> 00:15:52.419
It's hard for both of us.

192
00:15:53.128 --> 00:15:54.713
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

193
00:15:55.464 --> 00:15:58.050
Aren't they bastards from the peninsula?

194
00:15:58.133 --> 00:16:00.344
- What?
- Where the virus came from!

195
00:16:00.845 --> 00:16:02.972
Should you be letting them in here?

196
00:16:03.055 --> 00:16:04.056
Move aside.

197
00:16:04.139 --> 00:16:05.224
- Let go of me.
- Stop.

198
00:16:05.307 --> 00:16:06.766
Do you even care about the others?

199
00:16:06.851 --> 00:16:07.893
Stop it.

200
00:16:07.977 --> 00:16:10.520
Is he infected?

201
00:16:10.604 --> 00:16:12.106
Come on. Stop.

202
00:16:12.231 --> 00:16:14.149
I won't take your money. so just leave!

203
00:16:15.734 --> 00:16:16.902
You go ahead.

204
00:16:50.060 --> 00:16:52.187
You're entering the peninsula waters.

205
00:16:52.271 --> 00:16:53.397
Turn back.

206
00:16:53.730 --> 00:16:55.524
You're entering the peninsula waters.

207
00:16:55.607 --> 00:16:56.608
Turn back.

208
00:16:56.691 --> 00:16:59.444
This is Z055 Chungpyung.

209
00:17:02.031 --> 00:17:04.158
- Hello?
- Hello?

210
00:17:05.075 --> 00:17:06.743
It's all good if there's no response.

211
00:17:28.932 --> 00:17:30.392
Almost there!

212
00:17:33.312 --> 00:17:35.605
No need to be so serious.

213
00:17:35.689 --> 00:17:37.691
Soon. you'll be rich!

214
00:17:38.400 --> 00:17:39.651
Take what you need.

215
00:17:40.527 --> 00:17:44.865
Don't forget. the zombies are blind at night
and sensitive to sound.

216
00:17:45.740 --> 00:17:47.117
And the important thing.

217
00:17:47.659 --> 00:17:52.706
We'll drop you off
and stay at sea nearby for three days.

218
00:17:57.252 --> 00:17:58.337
Take these.

219
00:17:59.296 --> 00:18:00.297
One for you.

220
00:18:00.881 --> 00:18:03.968
And... another.

221
00:18:05.177 --> 00:18:07.304
Call me when you get to the port with the truck

222
00:18:07.387 --> 00:18:09.348
and we'll pull up the boat.

223
00:18:13.978 --> 00:18:15.229
And lastly!

224
00:18:15.855 --> 00:18:19.358
You escaped out of there alive.
so you know better...

225
00:18:19.900 --> 00:18:23.153
Don't screw up trying
to save each other for nothing.

226
00:18:23.612 --> 00:18:25.572
Don't worry. We know.

227
00:18:25.990 --> 00:18:26.991
Great!

228
00:18:27.657 --> 00:18:28.825
Do not let us down.

229
00:18:38.210 --> 00:18:41.671
It makes me nervous that you two know each other.

230
00:18:41.755 --> 00:18:43.132
I know.

231
00:18:43.883 --> 00:18:45.926
We have to pull this off no matter what.

232
00:18:46.010 --> 00:18:48.345
so don't let your personal emotions
get mixed up in the way.

233
00:18:48.720 --> 00:18:51.681
We won't even see each other after this.
so don't worry.

234
00:18:53.392 --> 00:18:54.434
Fine.

235
00:18:54.977 --> 00:18:56.061
Whatever. man.

236
00:20:21.230 --> 00:20:28.195
GOD HAS FORSAKEN US

237
00:20:48.757 --> 00:20:50.092
We're not on a tour. you know.

238
00:20:51.093 --> 00:20:54.221
Let's hurry things along.
we should leave before sunrise.

239
00:20:54.972 --> 00:20:56.640
All right. let's get it over with.

240
00:20:56.723 --> 00:20:58.225
Jeez.

241
00:21:03.022 --> 00:21:04.189
Is it working?

242
00:21:06.733 --> 00:21:08.110
Nice!

243
00:21:29.256 --> 00:21:31.341
It's unrecognizable now. My goodness.

244
00:21:31.841 --> 00:21:34.719
The city became a ruin in just four years.

245
00:21:35.470 --> 00:21:36.763
Did you live near here?

246
00:21:37.764 --> 00:21:40.642
I used to drive a cab.

247
00:21:41.143 --> 00:21:43.812
So I pretty much know all the roads.

248
00:21:45.064 --> 00:21:47.691
At the very least.
those jerks put together a good team.

249
00:21:58.743 --> 00:22:00.704
A HEALTHY. CAREFREE COUNTRY

250
00:22:23.643 --> 00:22:24.895
Could that be it?

251
00:22:25.145 --> 00:22:26.313
Where?

252
00:22:27.772 --> 00:22:29.608
The plate number is 6431. right?

253
00:22:30.192 --> 00:22:31.401
We'll find out soon.

254
00:22:31.986 --> 00:22:33.904
You stay here. I'll go alone.

255
00:22:33.988 --> 00:22:35.030
What?

256
00:22:35.114 --> 00:22:36.991
Hey. hey. hey! Wait!

257
00:23:43.348 --> 00:23:44.599
Come on. come on. come on!

258
00:23:45.767 --> 00:23:47.019
What's with you?

259
00:23:47.853 --> 00:23:49.021
Is that the truck?

260
00:23:49.771 --> 00:23:50.898
No. it isn't.

261
00:23:52.607 --> 00:23:54.734
It should be nearby.
Let's look around a bit more.

262
00:24:22.637 --> 00:24:25.057
There. I see one more.

263
00:24:26.934 --> 00:24:28.268
Let's check it out.

264
00:24:29.436 --> 00:24:30.687
Okay.

265
00:24:49.623 --> 00:24:53.335
I'll go have a look. You stay here.

266
00:24:53.418 --> 00:24:54.419
Stop it!

267
00:24:54.879 --> 00:24:56.171
I'm not on a tour. you know.

268
00:24:56.964 --> 00:24:58.090
We'll go together.

269
00:24:58.632 --> 00:24:59.633
Mister.

270
00:25:00.050 --> 00:25:01.801
Let's take a look.

271
00:25:23.323 --> 00:25:24.699
Are they Unit 631?

272
00:25:26.118 --> 00:25:28.745
No. They're not.

273
00:25:30.998 --> 00:25:32.917
Jackpot. we found it.

274
00:25:58.608 --> 00:25:59.693
It was true...

275
00:26:03.072 --> 00:26:05.074
What they said was true.

276
00:26:05.157 --> 00:26:07.284
It's all in US dollars. How much is all this?

277
00:26:08.118 --> 00:26:09.870
We confirmed it. so let's get going.

278
00:26:11.956 --> 00:26:12.957
Okay.

279
00:26:14.291 --> 00:26:15.292
Jeez.

280
00:26:17.127 --> 00:26:19.421
Hey! Over here!

281
00:26:22.216 --> 00:26:25.219
He must've been the last person to make contact.

282
00:26:27.762 --> 00:26:29.473
How unfortunate.

283
00:26:29.974 --> 00:26:31.934
He could've been a millionaire.

284
00:26:32.309 --> 00:26:33.894
But it's good for us.

285
00:26:34.186 --> 00:26:35.645
Let's pull him out and go.

286
00:26:38.107 --> 00:26:40.317
Oh. jeez...

287
00:26:41.526 --> 00:26:42.527
He stinks...

288
00:26:44.446 --> 00:26:46.698
Move your leg. Thank you.

289
00:26:47.199 --> 00:26:48.242
Thank you.

290
00:26:58.878 --> 00:26:59.879
Idiots.

291
00:27:09.679 --> 00:27:10.722
Are you okay?

292
00:27:11.181 --> 00:27:12.892
I'm fine. I wasn't bitten.

293
00:27:21.150 --> 00:27:23.527
Gosh. what are they up to?

294
00:27:38.250 --> 00:27:39.543
Get in the car. go!

295
00:27:42.421 --> 00:27:43.505
Back it up!

296
00:28:34.598 --> 00:28:35.850
Hurry. hurry. hurry!

297
00:28:35.933 --> 00:28:36.976
Come on. come on. come on!

298
00:28:37.059 --> 00:28:38.143
All right!

299
00:28:40.104 --> 00:28:40.855
Let's go!

300
00:28:40.855 --> 00:28:42.147
Go! Go!

301
00:28:50.364 --> 00:28:51.531
We're clear. we're clear!

302
00:28:51.740 --> 00:28:52.867
Thank you...

303
00:28:53.783 --> 00:28:56.370
So the money's really there?

304
00:28:57.412 --> 00:28:59.414
You're a millionaire!

305
00:29:01.625 --> 00:29:02.667
Yes!

306
00:29:02.751 --> 00:29:04.378
Awesome!

307
00:29:04.753 --> 00:29:06.088
What will you do with the money?

308
00:29:06.171 --> 00:29:07.631
Me? Uh...

309
00:29:07.714 --> 00:29:08.840
Maybe I'll hire a chauffeur.

310
00:29:08.924 --> 00:29:10.675
Like a real millionaire!

311
00:29:14.596 --> 00:29:16.598
So we just have to get
to the harbor and call them in.

312
00:29:18.058 --> 00:29:19.977
This is a piece of cake!

313
00:29:21.937 --> 00:29:23.147
Give me the satellite phone.

314
00:29:23.230 --> 00:29:24.940
Huh? Sure. hold on.

315
00:29:36.994 --> 00:29:38.745
Here.

316
00:29:41.165 --> 00:29:42.416
What's that?

317
00:30:03.478 --> 00:30:04.521
Just drive!

318
00:30:04.729 --> 00:30:06.523
Go. go. go! Just go!

319
00:31:52.837 --> 00:31:54.089
Hop in. if you want to live.

320
00:32:00.387 --> 00:32:01.430
Sorry!

321
00:32:29.041 --> 00:32:30.417
You must've been scared.

322
00:32:31.418 --> 00:32:35.714
Yu-jin. I told you not
to act so friendly to strangers.

323
00:32:36.882 --> 00:32:38.092
Sit back properly.

324
00:34:28.368 --> 00:34:29.786
Dang. he passed out.

325
00:34:30.620 --> 00:34:32.456
Did I not tell him to buckle up?

326
00:34:37.044 --> 00:34:39.796
Joon-i. can you drive through them?

327
00:34:41.924 --> 00:34:42.967
I'm not sure.

328
00:34:44.009 --> 00:34:46.846
Then what? Do I need to get involved?

329
00:35:35.769 --> 00:35:36.979
Ooh...

330
00:35:37.062 --> 00:35:38.438
Ooh.

331
00:35:49.116 --> 00:35:50.325
Uh?

332
00:35:58.667 --> 00:35:59.751
Really?

333
00:36:00.460 --> 00:36:03.881
The ground was weird. it wasn't my fault.

334
00:36:05.215 --> 00:36:06.716
Oh.

335
00:36:38.958 --> 00:36:41.501
I really liked that one. though.

336
00:37:08.653 --> 00:37:11.031
CITY NIGHT CLUB

337
00:37:53.073 --> 00:37:55.492
It's a grocery truck. Nice.

338
00:37:56.410 --> 00:37:57.786
It looks new.

339
00:38:02.707 --> 00:38:04.709
- Who's that?
- He's alive!

340
00:38:07.337 --> 00:38:10.090
- Please. help me...
- Be careful.

341
00:38:10.299 --> 00:38:13.886
- Be careful.
- Help me. I'm begging you...

342
00:38:17.681 --> 00:38:19.516
Help me. please.

343
00:38:19.599 --> 00:38:21.226
What the hell's going on?

344
00:38:21.726 --> 00:38:23.145
He's just an infected. you jerks.

345
00:38:23.270 --> 00:38:24.771
Have you never seen one before?

346
00:38:25.314 --> 00:38:26.315
Please...

347
00:38:26.398 --> 00:38:28.192
It's all right. come here.

348
00:38:48.753 --> 00:38:53.383
Sir. please. help me...

349
00:38:53.467 --> 00:38:56.053
I'm begging you...

350
00:39:00.099 --> 00:39:02.184
- Give it to me.
- Here you go!

351
00:39:05.020 --> 00:39:06.396
Sir...

352
00:39:09.608 --> 00:39:10.985
Nice shot!

353
00:39:11.193 --> 00:39:12.736
Wow. he killed him properly.

354
00:39:13.528 --> 00:39:14.654
Damn it!

355
00:39:16.615 --> 00:39:18.658
It got on my pants. I should get it washed.

356
00:39:19.326 --> 00:39:20.327
Here.

357
00:39:21.495 --> 00:39:22.746
Let's get back. the sun will rise.

358
00:39:23.288 --> 00:39:24.289
Shit...

359
00:39:24.664 --> 00:39:27.126
- Let's go.
- The zombies are coming!

360
00:39:29.669 --> 00:39:31.380
Huh?

361
00:39:52.317 --> 00:39:53.944
You little rascals!

362
00:39:54.278 --> 00:39:57.531
You brought something dangerous instead
of what you were supposed to get.

363
00:39:57.656 --> 00:39:58.698
Hey!

364
00:39:59.283 --> 00:40:02.827
You'd have been locked up for insubordination
if it were the old days!

365
00:40:09.543 --> 00:40:10.835
Lieutenant Yoon! Captain Hwang!

366
00:40:10.920 --> 00:40:11.921
Assemble!

367
00:40:12.421 --> 00:40:13.838
Aren't you going to make a report?

368
00:40:13.923 --> 00:40:15.424
Did you get what I asked?

369
00:40:15.715 --> 00:40:18.385
Salute! Division commander. we did not get it!

370
00:40:20.345 --> 00:40:21.346
Hey!

371
00:40:21.680 --> 00:40:23.015
How could you not get it?

372
00:40:23.098 --> 00:40:25.309
The ROK-US Combined Forces Command
is waiting for my call!

373
00:40:25.392 --> 00:40:26.685
Without batteries...

374
00:40:26.768 --> 00:40:27.895
Come on!

375
00:40:27.978 --> 00:40:29.563
- Are you having fun?
- Joon-i!

376
00:40:30.105 --> 00:40:31.648
- Captain Hwang!
- Grandpa!

377
00:40:32.274 --> 00:40:34.193
How long will you go on with that army stuff?

378
00:40:34.276 --> 00:40:35.277
Aren't you sick of it?

379
00:40:35.360 --> 00:40:36.611
No. it's for real this time!

380
00:40:36.695 --> 00:40:39.281
The newly appointed Major Jane
is totally different.

381
00:40:39.364 --> 00:40:40.991
She and I get along.

382
00:40:41.075 --> 00:40:44.036
And it seems like we'll get rescued soon.

383
00:40:44.119 --> 00:40:46.496
Listen to me. I'm good friends with her. so--

384
00:40:46.580 --> 00:40:48.540
- Stop it! I'm sick of it!
- Yu-jin. you believe me. right?

385
00:40:48.623 --> 00:40:49.624
Who are you?

386
00:40:52.586 --> 00:40:54.964
I guess you've never experienced
a wild dog hunt before.

387
00:40:55.047 --> 00:40:56.548
You should've known that such trucks

388
00:40:56.631 --> 00:40:58.217
would attract their attention.

389
00:40:58.550 --> 00:40:59.634
"Truck"?

390
00:40:59.718 --> 00:41:01.053
Who's that?

391
00:41:01.136 --> 00:41:02.137
Mom!

392
00:41:07.309 --> 00:41:11.480
Sir! Please!

393
00:41:13.523 --> 00:41:16.193
He was almost caught by Unit 631.

394
00:41:17.402 --> 00:41:18.778
You went outside again?

395
00:41:19.404 --> 00:41:21.115
I convinced her to go.

396
00:41:21.198 --> 00:41:22.782
Why don't you ever listen to me?

397
00:41:24.576 --> 00:41:25.744
I'm sorry. Mom.

398
00:41:27.496 --> 00:41:30.082
They're batteries. Grandpa. she got batteries!

399
00:41:31.791 --> 00:41:33.710
Okay! Okay!

400
00:41:36.421 --> 00:41:37.422
They fit.

401
00:41:37.506 --> 00:41:39.508
Hi. Jane? Jane? Major Jane?

402
00:41:40.092 --> 00:41:42.636
Oh. Jane! Oh. Jane! Okay!

403
00:41:44.471 --> 00:41:45.680
Are you okay?

404
00:41:45.764 --> 00:41:48.392
- I'm okay! Yeah!
- You should turn it on.

405
00:41:48.475 --> 00:41:49.894
We are strong soldiers! No problem!

406
00:41:49.977 --> 00:41:51.228
I'm Yu-jin!

407
00:41:53.522 --> 00:41:54.606
When are you coming?

408
00:41:54.689 --> 00:41:56.942
- So people still live here...
- They said they're coming!

409
00:41:58.735 --> 00:41:59.819
Who are you?

410
00:42:00.445 --> 00:42:01.780
Are you with Unit 631?

411
00:42:05.742 --> 00:42:07.786
I don't know what 631 is.

412
00:42:09.621 --> 00:42:11.831
I came to Incheon by boat yesterday.

413
00:42:13.042 --> 00:42:14.209
From Hong Kong.

414
00:42:14.668 --> 00:42:15.669
What?

415
00:42:16.795 --> 00:42:18.255
From where?

416
00:42:29.474 --> 00:42:31.185
Damn. the sun is rising.

417
00:42:32.602 --> 00:42:34.271
Let's hurry up.

418
00:42:39.443 --> 00:42:40.945
The third platoon is returning!

419
00:42:41.028 --> 00:42:42.404
Open the gate!

420
00:42:52.164 --> 00:42:54.624
There are one. two. three.
four. five. six boxes of cookies.

421
00:42:55.000 --> 00:42:56.210
That's all correct.

422
00:42:58.587 --> 00:42:59.922
Scrap soup again?

423
00:43:00.214 --> 00:43:01.340
Eat if you want to live.

424
00:43:01.423 --> 00:43:04.509
That looks good. Have a great meal!

425
00:43:04.593 --> 00:43:06.553
Have a nice meal. Have a nice meal.

426
00:43:08.763 --> 00:43:10.390
The third platoon is back!

427
00:43:10.474 --> 00:43:11.808
They're here!

428
00:43:21.776 --> 00:43:25.489
- They're back!
- They're here!

429
00:43:27.157 --> 00:43:29.368
Great work. everyone.

430
00:43:29.451 --> 00:43:31.120
Look! Isn't it awesome?

431
00:43:31.203 --> 00:43:32.829
- Yeah!
- It sure is.

432
00:43:32.913 --> 00:43:34.539
My boys worked so hard!

433
00:43:34.623 --> 00:43:36.959
Bring us a can of tuna. that's all I ask!

434
00:43:37.042 --> 00:43:38.252
- I'm sorry. sir...
- No. bring one.

435
00:43:38.335 --> 00:43:39.962
We were told to keep a tight lid on supplies.

436
00:43:40.045 --> 00:43:42.506
If I keep handing out stuff.
there won't be anything left.

437
00:43:42.589 --> 00:43:43.798
And Captain Seo is...

438
00:43:44.383 --> 00:43:45.550
One can is too much?

439
00:43:45.800 --> 00:43:46.801
That's not it...

440
00:43:47.136 --> 00:43:48.137
Bring it.

441
00:43:48.387 --> 00:43:49.429
They're serving food at the cafeteria.

442
00:43:49.513 --> 00:43:50.514
Get it!

443
00:43:50.597 --> 00:43:51.681
I said bring it!

444
00:43:51.932 --> 00:43:53.350
So I should just have scraps?

445
00:43:53.600 --> 00:43:54.643
That's not...

446
00:43:54.726 --> 00:43:55.727
Do you want it?

447
00:43:56.061 --> 00:43:58.188
I have to report to Captain Seo first.

448
00:43:58.813 --> 00:44:00.274
Just bring it. asshole!

449
00:44:01.483 --> 00:44:05.529
Report to a guy who's never even fought before?

450
00:44:05.946 --> 00:44:07.281
He's my commander.

451
00:44:07.364 --> 00:44:09.408
- Sergeant...
- Piss off. you bastard!

452
00:44:11.076 --> 00:44:12.827
- What was that?
- I'm talking here!

453
00:44:13.203 --> 00:44:14.704
- What was that?
- Hello?

454
00:44:15.122 --> 00:44:18.042
- Where is it coming from?
- I heard something.

455
00:44:21.045 --> 00:44:22.504
- What? A person?
- Hang on.

456
00:44:22.587 --> 00:44:25.132
Sir. we have a wild dog here.

457
00:44:25.966 --> 00:44:26.967
- What?
- Get him.

458
00:44:27.259 --> 00:44:28.552
What's a wild dog?

459
00:44:30.888 --> 00:44:32.264
Are you soldiers?

460
00:44:32.764 --> 00:44:35.142
Help me. I'm not from here.

461
00:44:36.268 --> 00:44:37.269
Get up. you bastard.

462
00:44:37.352 --> 00:44:38.812
Has the game started?

463
00:44:39.021 --> 00:44:40.064
It hasn't. sir.

464
00:44:40.147 --> 00:44:41.690
Take him to the arena.

465
00:44:41.773 --> 00:44:43.817
- Yes. sir.
- Let's go!

466
00:44:45.194 --> 00:44:46.904
We have a new player!

467
00:44:51.575 --> 00:44:55.996
Keep sucking up to Captain Seo.
and I'll kill you both.

468
00:44:56.080 --> 00:44:57.081
Got that?

469
00:44:59.083 --> 00:45:00.960
You little...

470
00:45:04.004 --> 00:45:05.130
Hey! Hey!

471
00:45:06.131 --> 00:45:07.549
He probably wasted all the flares

472
00:45:07.632 --> 00:45:09.134
without knowing what to get.

473
00:45:09.634 --> 00:45:10.719
That idiot.

474
00:45:11.136 --> 00:45:14.932
He brought so much useless crap last time.

475
00:45:19.937 --> 00:45:21.146
What the hell?

476
00:45:21.563 --> 00:45:23.357
We are strong soldiers!

477
00:45:23.648 --> 00:45:24.942
Strong! Strong!

478
00:45:25.860 --> 00:45:27.111
Strong. Strong.

479
00:45:28.362 --> 00:45:30.489
No one ever came to rescue us in four years.

480
00:45:31.531 --> 00:45:33.200
but some chump change was all it took?

481
00:45:36.120 --> 00:45:37.454
What about your group?

482
00:45:42.334 --> 00:45:43.418
They're all dead.

483
00:45:45.295 --> 00:45:46.380
Everyone.

484
00:45:48.757 --> 00:45:49.967
We got a fresh one!

485
00:46:04.523 --> 00:46:05.900
Hey there. cutie!

486
00:46:11.238 --> 00:46:12.614
Who were those soldiers?

487
00:46:12.697 --> 00:46:14.366
They're called Unit 631.

488
00:46:15.117 --> 00:46:17.369
They used to be a military unit dispatched
to rescue civilians.

489
00:46:17.912 --> 00:46:19.829
You were with them?

490
00:46:19.914 --> 00:46:22.291
We lived there before we escaped.

491
00:46:22.374 --> 00:46:23.876
At first.

492
00:46:25.669 --> 00:46:27.171
They sent out SOS signals for a few years.

493
00:46:27.254 --> 00:46:28.380
which were left unanswered.

494
00:46:29.589 --> 00:46:31.550
After that. they gave up everything.

495
00:46:31.675 --> 00:46:33.760
and now they're all crazy.

496
00:47:09.796 --> 00:47:11.131
Hm.

497
00:47:12.007 --> 00:47:13.092
I'm leaving.

498
00:47:22.267 --> 00:47:23.268
Yes?

499
00:47:32.069 --> 00:47:34.779
Bang!

500
00:47:36.240 --> 00:47:39.409
Awesome. that's great.

501
00:47:43.538 --> 00:47:45.916
I'm not someone who takes bribes. take it back.

502
00:47:46.041 --> 00:47:47.960
Gosh. you're making me sad.

503
00:47:48.043 --> 00:47:50.087
I don't take bribes!

504
00:47:50.170 --> 00:47:51.505
Look at it. it's Black Label.

505
00:47:52.631 --> 00:47:55.300
Thanks. I was finishing my last drink.

506
00:47:56.218 --> 00:47:58.720
Here. accept my drink.

507
00:48:07.062 --> 00:48:08.397
Nothing to report again?

508
00:48:08.480 --> 00:48:10.024
No. nothing happened.

509
00:48:10.607 --> 00:48:15.112
Sergeant Hwang stole a truck
from wild dogs overnight.

510
00:48:15.654 --> 00:48:18.949
and was boasting like crazy.

511
00:48:19.033 --> 00:48:21.035
acting all high and mighty...

512
00:48:21.869 --> 00:48:25.080
So where did our valiant sergeant go today

513
00:48:25.164 --> 00:48:27.707
and what adventure did he have?

514
00:48:29.834 --> 00:48:31.378
What did he bring in?

515
00:48:32.254 --> 00:48:35.007
Captain. that's the weird thing.

516
00:48:35.465 --> 00:48:37.134
The truck was full of US dollars.

517
00:48:37.217 --> 00:48:38.343
US dollars?

518
00:48:39.386 --> 00:48:40.387
How much?

519
00:48:41.305 --> 00:48:43.515
It was quite a bit.

520
00:48:43.891 --> 00:48:46.977
About 20 bags full of them.

521
00:48:47.561 --> 00:48:50.605
But why do you think those idiotic wild dogs

522
00:48:50.689 --> 00:48:53.859
were transporting completely useless money?

523
00:48:56.611 --> 00:48:57.863
Where is it now?

524
00:48:59.114 --> 00:49:00.908
So they took the truck.

525
00:49:01.658 --> 00:49:02.910
What about the satellite phone?

526
00:49:03.702 --> 00:49:05.745
It should be by the driver's seat.

527
00:49:14.213 --> 00:49:17.257
Sir. I'm not from here!

528
00:49:18.467 --> 00:49:20.552
I'm from Hong Kong!

529
00:49:22.471 --> 00:49:23.555
This is brand new.

530
00:49:23.638 --> 00:49:25.432
It's rare. Today is your lucky day.

531
00:49:25.515 --> 00:49:26.725
Got anything else?

532
00:49:26.976 --> 00:49:29.686
I have... a satellite phone!

533
00:49:31.063 --> 00:49:34.358
With a satellite phone.
we can all get out of here!

534
00:49:35.275 --> 00:49:36.818
- Show us!
- Right here!

535
00:49:37.194 --> 00:49:39.529
- You lying sack of shit!
- He doesn't have it!

536
00:49:44.618 --> 00:49:47.121
Where do you think they
were heading with this money?

537
00:49:54.419 --> 00:49:56.130
Sir. where's the truck?

538
00:49:57.381 --> 00:49:58.715
Stop that!

539
00:49:59.049 --> 00:50:00.300
Stop! Please!

540
00:50:02.344 --> 00:50:03.888
Ah...

541
00:50:11.979 --> 00:50:13.063
He's really fresh!

542
00:50:13.147 --> 00:50:16.233
This guy's in good shape. He's a Grade A!

543
00:50:19.778 --> 00:50:20.905
Can you run well?

544
00:50:21.488 --> 00:50:22.489
No?

545
00:50:25.700 --> 00:50:26.869
What should his number be?

546
00:50:26.952 --> 00:50:28.245
Give him Park Chan-ho's number.

547
00:50:28.328 --> 00:50:29.329
Number 61!

548
00:50:29.413 --> 00:50:30.747
Number 61 it is!

549
00:50:30.830 --> 00:50:34.793
Major League pitcher!

550
00:50:35.460 --> 00:50:36.586
That's a great number!

551
00:50:41.466 --> 00:50:42.592
Turn around!

552
00:50:45.554 --> 00:50:47.932
I'm betting a chocolate bar on him.

553
00:50:53.103 --> 00:50:55.189
Sir. where's the truck?

554
00:51:07.159 --> 00:51:10.454
Sir! I'm not from here!

555
00:51:11.080 --> 00:51:13.040
There's money in the truck! Go check it out!

556
00:51:13.123 --> 00:51:16.001
We can all leave if we have that. you idiots!

557
00:51:37.022 --> 00:51:38.023
What...

558
00:51:43.195 --> 00:51:44.238
Hello?

559
00:51:44.321 --> 00:51:45.822
Where are you? The sun is out.

560
00:51:46.240 --> 00:51:47.366
What's going on?

561
00:51:48.700 --> 00:51:50.870
Hello. Who are you?

562
00:51:51.161 --> 00:51:52.162
What?

563
00:51:52.246 --> 00:51:53.538
Who the hell are you?

564
00:51:53.705 --> 00:51:54.957
Where's the money?

565
00:52:21.316 --> 00:52:22.526
Where are you going?

566
00:52:23.610 --> 00:52:24.945
I don't think we should go out...

567
00:52:28.615 --> 00:52:30.700
Number 61! Get out!

568
00:52:32.452 --> 00:52:33.620
Get the hell out!

569
00:53:07.071 --> 00:53:08.572
I don't care who you are.

570
00:53:08.655 --> 00:53:09.656
Just bring the money.

571
00:53:09.739 --> 00:53:12.034
The terms are the same
as the guys we sent in...

572
00:53:12.284 --> 00:53:15.454
Half the money to anyone
that brings it out. Okay?

573
00:53:16.163 --> 00:53:19.541
Are you saying we can get out of here?

574
00:53:19.624 --> 00:53:21.501
We are waiting around Incheon Port.

575
00:53:21.585 --> 00:53:23.128
You call me when you get there.

576
00:53:23.795 --> 00:53:24.838
It's so easy!

577
00:53:25.630 --> 00:53:27.883
Easy. easy. I can do it. I can do it.

578
00:53:27.967 --> 00:53:29.009
All right.

579
00:53:36.516 --> 00:53:38.018
You can drive. right?

580
00:53:39.186 --> 00:53:41.188
Let's just go now. Mom.

581
00:53:42.147 --> 00:53:44.149
I'll bulldoze them all with my car.

582
00:53:46.776 --> 00:53:49.654
You'll just go in there? In broad daylight?

583
00:55:04.563 --> 00:55:06.815
Run faster!

584
00:55:26.376 --> 00:55:30.380
It's time for us. To say goodbye

585
00:55:30.755 --> 00:55:33.217
Let's meet again soon

586
00:55:34.718 --> 00:55:38.722
It's time for us. To say goodbye

587
00:55:39.056 --> 00:55:41.641
Let's meet again soon

588
00:55:44.353 --> 00:55:45.562
Hey. buddy!

589
00:55:46.771 --> 00:55:48.398
If you don't hurry. the doors will shut!

590
00:56:15.675 --> 00:56:16.927
You must be tired.

591
00:56:17.094 --> 00:56:18.345
You did great.

592
00:56:18.428 --> 00:56:19.804
How about a feast?

593
00:56:20.014 --> 00:56:21.431
You want it? Really?

594
00:56:22.557 --> 00:56:24.226
Have some ramen!

595
00:56:24.643 --> 00:56:26.896
Eat slowly! Share them with your friends!

596
00:56:26.979 --> 00:56:28.272
Greedy bastards.

597
00:56:33.485 --> 00:56:34.611
You should share them!

598
00:56:36.571 --> 00:56:39.867
It's too dangerous now.
Let's move after sundown.

599
00:56:39.950 --> 00:56:42.619
I think we can go now. though...

600
00:56:43.495 --> 00:56:45.080
Go? Go where?

601
00:56:46.456 --> 00:56:48.876
Grandpa. we're moving. Let's pack up.

602
00:56:49.168 --> 00:56:50.210
Move?

603
00:56:50.752 --> 00:56:51.753
Where?

604
00:56:51.836 --> 00:56:53.547
We're going to Incheon Port.

605
00:56:53.630 --> 00:56:55.257
Incheon Port? Are we going to ride a boat?

606
00:56:55.340 --> 00:56:56.341
Okay!

607
00:56:56.425 --> 00:56:57.551
No. no. no!

608
00:56:57.968 --> 00:57:01.346
We must stay here until Jane
comes to rescue us.

609
00:57:01.430 --> 00:57:03.223
It was so hard convincing her!

610
00:57:03.307 --> 00:57:05.976
If Major Jane is coming.
tell her to come to the port.

611
00:57:06.060 --> 00:57:07.394
No way!

612
00:57:07.477 --> 00:57:08.854
You said you two are close.

613
00:57:09.646 --> 00:57:11.190
I guess you aren't.

614
00:57:11.982 --> 00:57:12.983
We're close.

615
00:57:13.192 --> 00:57:14.985
Okay. it's doable.

616
00:57:15.735 --> 00:57:17.196
Incheon? Incheon Port?

617
00:57:17.279 --> 00:57:19.364
- Grandpa. hurry!
- Okay.

618
00:57:21.951 --> 00:57:24.744
You'll take a crazy old man and little kids

619
00:57:26.330 --> 00:57:28.790
to steal a truck from armed soldiers?

620
00:57:29.791 --> 00:57:32.878
Then should I continue living here with my girls?

621
00:57:34.254 --> 00:57:36.131
If you're scared. stay here.

622
00:57:37.799 --> 00:57:39.343
I'll give you this place at a cheap price.

623
00:57:41.720 --> 00:57:43.430
Get him a first aid kit.

624
00:57:44.264 --> 00:57:46.391
and get some sleep. We'll leave after sundown.

625
00:58:06.120 --> 00:58:07.662
Why did you save me earlier?

626
00:58:08.998 --> 00:58:11.458
I was going to leave. but she wanted to save you.

627
00:58:12.459 --> 00:58:16.255
Dad told us we should help the weak
before he went to heaven.

628
00:58:17.422 --> 00:58:19.299
You looked weak.

629
00:58:21.551 --> 00:58:23.512
Stop yapping and go to bed.

630
00:58:23.595 --> 00:58:24.596
No!

631
00:58:24.679 --> 00:58:26.598
I'm going to bed soon too. so go to sleep!

632
00:58:26.681 --> 00:58:27.807
I don't want to!

633
00:58:28.225 --> 00:58:29.935
One! Two!

634
00:58:31.395 --> 00:58:32.521
She's always like that...

635
00:58:32.604 --> 00:58:34.148
She thinks she's so big now.

636
00:58:35.815 --> 00:58:37.401
Maybe we should've left you there.

637
00:58:38.027 --> 00:58:39.736
You're complaining when we saved you.

638
00:58:40.820 --> 00:58:42.281
You look like a zombie.

639
00:58:48.328 --> 00:58:50.664
Mm...

640
00:58:51.916 --> 00:58:54.001
How long does it take to get to Incheon Port?

641
00:58:54.084 --> 00:58:55.377
If we find an unobstructed route.

642
00:58:55.460 --> 00:58:56.836
it'll only take thirty minutes.

643
00:58:57.171 --> 00:58:59.131
Thirty minutes. thirty minutes. thirty minutes...

644
00:59:00.090 --> 00:59:01.633
What about zombies? Wouldn't it be dangerous?

645
00:59:01.716 --> 00:59:02.885
They bite and stuff.

646
00:59:02.968 --> 00:59:04.136
- Captain.
- Yes?

647
00:59:04.845 --> 00:59:06.638
We need to get out of here.

648
00:59:06.763 --> 00:59:08.640
Forget about the zombies!

649
00:59:09.558 --> 00:59:11.310
Should we bring Sergeant Hwang?

650
00:59:12.019 --> 00:59:14.563
He's more dangerous than the zombies.

651
00:59:14.646 --> 00:59:15.647
You're right.

652
00:59:15.730 --> 00:59:18.275
I can keep the gatekeepers off our backs.

653
00:59:18.859 --> 00:59:22.404
but sharp-witted Sergeant Hwang
might get suspicious.

654
00:59:24.323 --> 00:59:26.158
Yes. you're right.

655
00:59:27.201 --> 00:59:33.207
Then I just have to find a way
to distract him. right?

656
01:00:14.957 --> 01:00:16.500
Sir? Sir!

657
01:00:17.084 --> 01:00:19.419
Sir! Please!

658
01:00:19.962 --> 01:00:23.966
Sir! Please just take my girl!

659
01:00:27.469 --> 01:00:31.015
Jung-seok. why are you the only one alive?

660
01:01:05.382 --> 01:01:06.591
Put it down.

661
01:01:08.010 --> 01:01:09.261
You'll drain the batteries.

662
01:01:13.765 --> 01:01:16.601
Did Major Jane say she's coming to Incheon Port?

663
01:01:16.685 --> 01:01:17.769
Huh?

664
01:01:20.856 --> 01:01:23.817
She should. She has to.

665
01:01:26.153 --> 01:01:28.405
She better rescue my little darlings.

666
01:01:28.864 --> 01:01:30.324
My treasures.

667
01:01:31.491 --> 01:01:33.202
Yu-jin and Joon-i.

668
01:01:34.411 --> 01:01:37.164
they're the beacon of hope in this hell.

669
01:01:40.084 --> 01:01:45.255
I'll get them out of this hell no matter what.

670
01:01:48.425 --> 01:01:51.136
Major Jane is coming. right?

671
01:02:12.824 --> 01:02:13.868
Are you okay?

672
01:02:14.994 --> 01:02:18.663
We stole these when we fled. Take what you need.

673
01:02:22.001 --> 01:02:24.128
I actually saw you before.

674
01:02:24.920 --> 01:02:25.921
I...

675
01:02:26.505 --> 01:02:29.925
came across your family
when I was fleeing to board the ship.

676
01:02:31.635 --> 01:02:33.345
You begged me to take your girl.

677
01:02:38.142 --> 01:02:40.019
Why are you telling me that now?

678
01:02:41.436 --> 01:02:42.479
Because you feel guilty?

679
01:02:43.563 --> 01:02:44.773
There were 31 cars.

680
01:02:45.858 --> 01:02:47.734
There were 31 cars that drove past us.

681
01:02:48.944 --> 01:02:50.863
I thought the first car would stop to help us.

682
01:02:51.446 --> 01:02:52.822
Or maybe the next one...

683
01:02:57.119 --> 01:02:58.871
All 31 cars just drove by.

684
01:03:01.831 --> 01:03:03.542
You're indebted to my girls.

685
01:03:09.173 --> 01:03:11.508
Yu-jin. I'm buttoning you up.
Stand up straight!

686
01:03:12.634 --> 01:03:15.804
Are we going on a boat ride now?

687
01:03:15.888 --> 01:03:18.891
Yes. we just have to get something first.

688
01:03:22.602 --> 01:03:23.770
What about my cars?

689
01:03:24.104 --> 01:03:26.606
No way. we can't take them all.

690
01:03:30.027 --> 01:03:31.403
Then just this one!

691
01:03:31.736 --> 01:03:32.779
Put it down.

692
01:03:32.863 --> 01:03:34.531
Please. just one!

693
01:03:35.240 --> 01:03:36.867
Let me take one!

694
01:03:40.412 --> 01:03:41.455
Let's go.

695
01:04:32.047 --> 01:04:33.132
Joon-i.

696
01:04:33.883 --> 01:04:37.970
Stay here. If I'm not back by sunrise.
head back home.

697
01:04:38.595 --> 01:04:39.763
Just the three of us?

698
01:04:40.514 --> 01:04:41.723
What about you?

699
01:04:42.307 --> 01:04:43.600
How will you come home?

700
01:04:44.559 --> 01:04:46.436
I'll find my way somehow.

701
01:04:46.561 --> 01:04:48.313
so don't worry and head home.

702
01:04:50.232 --> 01:04:54.694
And don't ever leave the car. got it?

703
01:04:56.738 --> 01:04:57.739
Answer me.

704
01:04:59.909 --> 01:05:00.910
Okay.

705
01:05:02.912 --> 01:05:04.371
Yu-jin. come here.

706
01:05:08.250 --> 01:05:12.296
I'll be back soon. Listen to your sister. okay?

707
01:05:12.880 --> 01:05:14.839
You'll really be back soon. right?

708
01:05:15.132 --> 01:05:16.508
Of course. I'll be right back.

709
01:05:28.938 --> 01:05:32.066
Commander. take good care of my girls.

710
01:05:37.196 --> 01:05:38.238
Let's go.

711
01:06:40.092 --> 01:06:42.511
It's an emergency exit that we found
when we lived here.

712
01:07:18.255 --> 01:07:19.464
What the hell?

713
01:07:37.482 --> 01:07:38.567
Is that it?

714
01:07:42.071 --> 01:07:43.572
Yes. that's the one.

715
01:07:44.990 --> 01:07:46.158
Let's move quickly.

716
01:07:49.661 --> 01:07:51.496
Ah. ah. ah.

717
01:07:51.580 --> 01:07:54.249
I brought good news.

718
01:07:56.293 --> 01:08:02.424
Last night. the third platoon led by Sergeant Hwang

719
01:08:02.507 --> 01:08:03.968
brought home a truck.

720
01:08:04.593 --> 01:08:08.848
There was enough food for everyone to eat

721
01:08:08.931 --> 01:08:10.474
for an entire month.

722
01:08:15.479 --> 01:08:17.522
You've worked so hard. I know you did!

723
01:08:17.606 --> 01:08:22.651
So tonight... there'll be an unlimited game

724
01:08:22.736 --> 01:08:24.446
for 24 hours!

725
01:08:27.074 --> 01:08:29.451
And remember.

726
01:08:29.909 --> 01:08:32.079
Have fun like there's no tomorrow.

727
01:08:32.204 --> 01:08:33.372
Have a great time!

728
01:08:37.416 --> 01:08:40.544
There will be no tomorrow.

729
01:08:40.837 --> 01:08:44.591
Stop cheering. Doesn't he seem strange?

730
01:08:44.716 --> 01:08:45.842
I think he's high.

731
01:08:45.925 --> 01:08:48.387
I'm not sure. Let's enjoy this!

732
01:08:53.307 --> 01:08:55.853
Hey. look over there.

733
01:08:56.395 --> 01:08:57.521
Shouldn't we report that?

734
01:08:58.022 --> 01:09:01.025
There aren't that many. Why bother reporting?

735
01:09:01.859 --> 01:09:03.152
Forget it. don't mind them.

736
01:09:37.519 --> 01:09:38.645
Listen.

737
01:09:39.438 --> 01:09:41.190
Since you owe my girls.

738
01:09:42.649 --> 01:09:44.651
do me a favor later.

739
01:09:59.083 --> 01:10:02.836
Johnnie Walker Black Label!

740
01:10:06.173 --> 01:10:07.257
You're back.

741
01:10:08.675 --> 01:10:12.304
Are you supposed to have booze here?

742
01:10:12.387 --> 01:10:13.430
Well...

743
01:10:13.680 --> 01:10:17.059
The game is about to start. What brings you here?

744
01:10:17.142 --> 01:10:20.020
I haven't seen your face in ages.

745
01:10:20.896 --> 01:10:23.983
Could I have a sip?

746
01:10:24.066 --> 01:10:25.400
Sure. help yourself.

747
01:10:25.484 --> 01:10:26.651
- Really?
- Sure.

748
01:10:27.694 --> 01:10:29.947
So why are you here?

749
01:10:30.114 --> 01:10:32.407
Do you have something to report?

750
01:10:32.491 --> 01:10:36.912
No. I was just curious
what gets you up in the morning.

751
01:10:38.956 --> 01:10:40.332
Hm?

752
01:10:47.214 --> 01:10:48.257
It's good?

753
01:10:48.465 --> 01:10:49.716
So good!

754
01:10:51.593 --> 01:10:54.889
If you love it that much.
you can take the bottle.

755
01:10:55.472 --> 01:10:56.723
It's my gift to you.

756
01:10:58.517 --> 01:11:00.269
- What's with you?
- What?

757
01:11:01.353 --> 01:11:04.523
I begged for some snacks
for my boys to boost morale.

758
01:11:04.606 --> 01:11:06.358
but all we got were scraps.

759
01:11:07.359 --> 01:11:08.944
You were acting so cheap.

760
01:11:10.779 --> 01:11:12.489
So why the sudden generosity?

761
01:11:13.657 --> 01:11:16.201
I think I told everyone with my speech earlier.

762
01:11:17.119 --> 01:11:21.540
We owe so much to you and your men...

763
01:11:21.623 --> 01:11:22.666
Bullshit!

764
01:11:26.086 --> 01:11:29.298
I was just kidding.

765
01:11:30.507 --> 01:11:34.469
Captain Seo. are you hiding something from me?

766
01:11:36.471 --> 01:11:38.348
No. of course not.

767
01:11:41.601 --> 01:11:42.853
Captain Seo. I...

768
01:11:45.522 --> 01:11:46.606
Private Kim?

769
01:11:47.983 --> 01:11:50.652
Do you visit Captain Seo's quarters frequently?

770
01:11:52.404 --> 01:11:54.865
No... I do not.

771
01:12:19.264 --> 01:12:21.683
Ah.

772
01:12:23.435 --> 01:12:24.603
You two are a thing?

773
01:12:26.146 --> 01:12:27.814
- Yes.
- My apologies!

774
01:12:30.275 --> 01:12:32.777
I'm so clueless.

775
01:12:33.612 --> 01:12:34.738
I'll leave you two alone.

776
01:12:35.906 --> 01:12:37.032
Just the two of you...

777
01:12:37.116 --> 01:12:39.326
Hm?

778
01:12:40.119 --> 01:12:43.413
I'll tell the boys to avoid dropping in.

779
01:12:43.497 --> 01:12:44.664
so have a great time.

780
01:12:44.748 --> 01:12:48.252
Have a hot time. okay?

781
01:12:48.961 --> 01:12:50.004
All right.

782
01:12:50.795 --> 01:12:52.756
Love. love is...

783
01:12:54.674 --> 01:12:56.886
Sir. the preparation is done.
Shall we get to the truck?

784
01:12:56.969 --> 01:12:59.346
You go ahead. I have something to do first.

785
01:12:59.429 --> 01:13:00.430
Yes. sir.

786
01:13:02.641 --> 01:13:04.768
Does he have a death wish or what?

787
01:13:15.320 --> 01:13:18.866
Joon-i. look up ahead! Quickly!

788
01:13:28.833 --> 01:13:29.960
It's a march.

789
01:13:39.719 --> 01:13:42.056
That road is too close to Unit 631.

790
01:13:42.139 --> 01:13:43.849
Aren't we going to go greet Mom?

791
01:14:15.589 --> 01:14:16.798
The money is intact.

792
01:14:38.946 --> 01:14:41.949
Hey. can't you take me with you?

793
01:14:42.616 --> 01:14:44.076
I really want to get out of here.

794
01:14:45.327 --> 01:14:47.704
Go where? Who told you about that?

795
01:14:48.663 --> 01:14:51.625
I overheard Captain Seo talking
on the satellite phone.

796
01:14:52.376 --> 01:14:53.793
Please take me with you.

797
01:14:54.211 --> 01:14:55.545
Satellite phone?

798
01:14:56.171 --> 01:14:57.464
Where did you get it?

799
01:14:57.839 --> 01:15:00.259
The wild dog we found in the truck had it.

800
01:15:01.093 --> 01:15:02.261
Private Kim!

801
01:15:02.344 --> 01:15:03.846
Aren't you going to see the game?

802
01:15:05.222 --> 01:15:06.640
Answer naturally.

803
01:15:09.768 --> 01:15:10.936
I'm all right.

804
01:15:11.436 --> 01:15:13.105
You always say that. Oh. right.

805
01:15:13.522 --> 01:15:16.108
That wild dog who came with the truck.

806
01:15:16.191 --> 01:15:17.817
that guy was no joke.

807
01:15:18.193 --> 01:15:21.446
He was struggling so much to survive.

808
01:15:22.614 --> 01:15:24.533
I bet all my canned goods on him!

809
01:15:25.409 --> 01:15:26.493
I'll see you later.

810
01:15:28.245 --> 01:15:29.829
Where is the phone now?

811
01:15:30.289 --> 01:15:31.790
It's not with me.

812
01:15:31.874 --> 01:15:33.458
Captain Seo has it. He'll be here soon.

813
01:15:37.587 --> 01:15:38.797
Get going.

814
01:15:39.839 --> 01:15:41.133
I can't wait long.

815
01:15:47.514 --> 01:15:50.559
Act naturally when that bastard comes. got it?

816
01:15:52.186 --> 01:15:53.270
Okay...

817
01:15:54.771 --> 01:15:57.232
Number 61!

818
01:16:19.880 --> 01:16:21.256
What are you doing? Let's move!

819
01:16:23.217 --> 01:16:24.509
Captain...

820
01:16:25.970 --> 01:16:27.512
Long time no see. Captain Seo.

821
01:16:29.223 --> 01:16:31.391
Min-jung. you were alive. Gosh.

822
01:16:32.434 --> 01:16:34.228
You have the satellite phone. right?

823
01:16:34.311 --> 01:16:35.437
Hand it over.

824
01:16:37.397 --> 01:16:38.648
The satellite phone...

825
01:16:39.316 --> 01:16:40.442
Give me a second.

826
01:16:41.276 --> 01:16:42.862
Mm. Oh.

827
01:16:56.625 --> 01:16:57.667
Wasn't that a gunshot?

828
01:16:57.751 --> 01:16:59.503
Like hell it was. Just shut up and eat this tuna.

829
01:16:59.586 --> 01:17:00.629
Hey!

830
01:17:05.634 --> 01:17:06.676
Oh.

831
01:17:09.054 --> 01:17:10.139
Let's go get Mom.

832
01:17:27.114 --> 01:17:28.908
Look! That bastard!

833
01:17:33.787 --> 01:17:35.247
Gun! Get the guns!

834
01:17:38.833 --> 01:17:40.544
- Are you okay?
- Yes...

835
01:17:41.211 --> 01:17:42.212
Can you get up?

836
01:17:42.671 --> 01:17:44.589
Yes. I can get up. I can get up.

837
01:17:51.931 --> 01:17:53.182
Stay behind me.

838
01:17:55.809 --> 01:17:58.187
Hey. where did he go?

839
01:17:58.520 --> 01:17:59.521
Jesus Christ...

840
01:18:01.773 --> 01:18:04.985
Min-jung. I was so worried...

841
01:18:07.071 --> 01:18:08.989
That's mine. give it back...

842
01:18:12.868 --> 01:18:13.911
Sergeant!

843
01:18:15.955 --> 01:18:17.622
Where did that bastard go?

844
01:18:21.919 --> 01:18:23.128
Go look for him.

845
01:18:30.594 --> 01:18:31.761
Block the entrance!

846
01:18:35.933 --> 01:18:36.976
Move!

847
01:19:26.942 --> 01:19:28.152
Fire! Fire!

848
01:19:55.262 --> 01:19:56.638
Hey. Go forward.

849
01:20:25.792 --> 01:20:26.793
Damn it!

850
01:20:26.961 --> 01:20:27.962
Jung-seok!

851
01:20:43.810 --> 01:20:44.895
Sergeant!

852
01:21:28.939 --> 01:21:30.149
Come on!

853
01:22:14.318 --> 01:22:16.904
Hurry! Get in!

854
01:22:21.533 --> 01:22:23.410
Get in! Come on!

855
01:22:27.622 --> 01:22:28.999
Snap out of it!

856
01:22:29.708 --> 01:22:30.960
Come on!

857
01:22:32.377 --> 01:22:33.462
Hurry!

858
01:22:53.858 --> 01:22:56.861
Go after them!

859
01:23:11.625 --> 01:23:13.418
Captain. are you okay?

860
01:23:16.546 --> 01:23:17.714
What do we do now. sir?

861
01:23:21.010 --> 01:23:22.094
Captain!

862
01:23:30.352 --> 01:23:32.021
You did all you can.

863
01:23:32.521 --> 01:23:33.813
That's what matters.

864
01:23:34.148 --> 01:23:35.274
Get it together.

865
01:24:00.215 --> 01:24:01.300
Sergeant Hwang!

866
01:24:03.302 --> 01:24:04.386
Step on it!

867
01:24:07.722 --> 01:24:11.560
It's time for us. To say goodbye

868
01:24:12.186 --> 01:24:14.229
Let's meet again soon

869
01:25:28.220 --> 01:25:29.304
Grandpa. hurry!

870
01:25:29.679 --> 01:25:31.056
Okay!

871
01:25:34.476 --> 01:25:35.727
Open the window.

872
01:25:59.001 --> 01:26:00.377
Mom!

873
01:26:00.878 --> 01:26:03.505
We came to greet you!

874
01:26:03.588 --> 01:26:05.840
Why don't you ever listen to me?

875
01:26:07.092 --> 01:26:08.218
Come on!

876
01:26:22.232 --> 01:26:23.442
Yee-haw!

877
01:26:48.717 --> 01:26:50.845
- Hold on.
- Okay!

878
01:27:19.789 --> 01:27:24.879
Hey! Stop with the damn flares!
Just kill them all!

879
01:27:44.814 --> 01:27:45.941
They're behind us!

880
01:27:52.322 --> 01:27:53.490
Hold on tight!

881
01:28:07.004 --> 01:28:08.213
Come on!

882
01:28:18.265 --> 01:28:20.184
You asshole!

883
01:28:28.483 --> 01:28:29.693
He's not bad.

884
01:29:16.156 --> 01:29:18.117
Pull up closer. asshole!

885
01:29:18.200 --> 01:29:19.618
This way. move up!

886
01:29:20.785 --> 01:29:21.786
Kill him!

887
01:29:37.302 --> 01:29:38.762
Watch the front. asshole!

888
01:29:39.138 --> 01:29:40.222
Hold the wheel!

889
01:29:42.224 --> 01:29:43.225
Hey!

890
01:29:53.443 --> 01:29:54.528
Turn on the lights.

891
01:30:20.220 --> 01:30:21.471
To our right!

892
01:30:38.280 --> 01:30:39.323
Beside you!

893
01:31:03.513 --> 01:31:04.514
Watch out!

894
01:31:49.977 --> 01:31:51.103
Hold on tight!

895
01:33:04.885 --> 01:33:06.220
Go over to the right!

896
01:33:37.459 --> 01:33:39.753
Hey! Back up. back up. back up!

897
01:33:45.509 --> 01:33:47.719
Back it up!

898
01:33:49.179 --> 01:33:52.099
I said back it up. asshole!

899
01:33:55.810 --> 01:33:57.604
Just step on it!

900
01:33:58.688 --> 01:34:01.025
Back the shit up!

901
01:34:01.816 --> 01:34:03.693
What the hell are you doing? Back it up!

902
01:34:07.781 --> 01:34:08.866
You bastard!

903
01:34:34.975 --> 01:34:36.268
We're almost there.

904
01:34:46.445 --> 01:34:49.114
We arrive at Incheon Port in 15 minutes.

905
01:35:24.316 --> 01:35:25.317
Joon-i.

906
01:35:25.943 --> 01:35:28.737
Is that the boat? Oh. yes!

907
01:35:39.915 --> 01:35:40.958
Yu-jin...

908
01:35:41.750 --> 01:35:42.877
Yu-jin. are you okay?

909
01:35:44.169 --> 01:35:45.212
Hi.

910
01:35:48.590 --> 01:35:49.591
Joon-i!

911
01:35:52.386 --> 01:35:54.804
Put down your gun! Come on!

912
01:35:56.806 --> 01:35:57.892
Drop it!

913
01:35:58.433 --> 01:36:00.435
Do you want to see her head blown up?

914
01:36:00.519 --> 01:36:01.603
Put it down!

915
01:36:06.650 --> 01:36:09.069
Kick it! Kick it away!

916
01:36:09.987 --> 01:36:11.405
Yes. that's it.

917
01:36:15.409 --> 01:36:17.494
I can finally get off this peninsula...

918
01:36:18.203 --> 01:36:23.250
When I leave. I'm going to live
to the fullest in Hong Kong.

919
01:36:25.627 --> 01:36:28.630
They won't know what I did here.

920
01:36:29.006 --> 01:36:30.966
I'm going to be a good man.

921
01:36:31.716 --> 01:36:35.137
Thank you. Thank you so much.

922
01:36:35.220 --> 01:36:36.805
I'll thank you every night.

923
01:36:37.264 --> 01:36:39.433
I really mean it. Thank you so much.

924
01:36:39.516 --> 01:36:41.936
I love you all!

925
01:36:42.019 --> 01:36:43.020
Now!

926
01:36:46.023 --> 01:36:47.024
Okay...

927
01:36:53.113 --> 01:36:54.114
No!

928
01:37:25.479 --> 01:37:26.939
Grandpa...

929
01:37:27.898 --> 01:37:30.650
Grandpa. are you okay?

930
01:37:31.026 --> 01:37:32.277
Grandpa...

931
01:37:32.486 --> 01:37:34.071
Mom! Mom...

932
01:38:07.687 --> 01:38:08.772
The sun is rising.

933
01:38:08.856 --> 01:38:09.857
A horde's coming.

934
01:38:10.440 --> 01:38:11.608
We have to depart!

935
01:38:23.537 --> 01:38:24.621
The money's here.

936
01:38:27.917 --> 01:38:28.918
Huh?

937
01:38:30.002 --> 01:38:31.545
It's not him.

938
01:38:33.005 --> 01:38:34.714
How many times did they switch?

939
01:38:37.634 --> 01:38:38.844
Nice to meet you...

940
01:38:39.469 --> 01:38:41.680
- Nice to meet you too.
- Thank you.

941
01:38:49.229 --> 01:38:52.274
Get rid of the body!

942
01:39:06.496 --> 01:39:09.959
Hey. stop!

943
01:39:19.969 --> 01:39:22.888
Get the money!

944
01:39:22.972 --> 01:39:25.891
Shut the back hatch! Zombies are coming!

945
01:39:58.548 --> 01:40:01.260
Grandpa...

946
01:40:03.971 --> 01:40:06.849
Okay. I'm okay...

947
01:40:07.349 --> 01:40:09.601
Grandpa...

948
01:40:13.438 --> 01:40:16.441
I wanted to pull you out of this hell...

949
01:40:19.694 --> 01:40:20.863
No...

950
01:40:22.322 --> 01:40:25.034
We were together all along.

951
01:40:26.493 --> 01:40:28.495
Why would this be hell?

952
01:40:30.539 --> 01:40:31.581
Thank you...

953
01:40:32.499 --> 01:40:34.418
Grandpa...

954
01:40:38.463 --> 01:40:40.090
Grandpa!

955
01:40:41.675 --> 01:40:43.135
I'm sorry...

956
01:40:44.636 --> 01:40:46.931
for making you live in this world...

957
01:40:47.306 --> 01:40:49.433
Grandpa...

958
01:40:51.060 --> 01:40:54.897
- Grandpa...
- I'm sorry...

959
01:40:55.147 --> 01:40:56.565
Grandpa.

960
01:41:02.154 --> 01:41:03.613
Grandpa!

961
01:41:08.743 --> 01:41:10.495
Don't die...

962
01:41:15.584 --> 01:41:18.295
Grandpa! No!

963
01:41:20.714 --> 01:41:22.257
Grandpa...

964
01:42:02.839 --> 01:42:04.549
Girls! The fireworks!

965
01:42:04.633 --> 01:42:05.675
Hurry!

966
01:42:07.136 --> 01:42:08.137
Joon-i!

967
01:42:14.726 --> 01:42:18.147
You promised to do a favor for me.

968
01:42:19.481 --> 01:42:22.442
Take the girls with you no matter what.

969
01:42:23.277 --> 01:42:24.319
Got it?

970
01:42:24.653 --> 01:42:25.654
Promise me. okay?

971
01:42:26.405 --> 01:42:27.447
Get going!

972
01:42:28.240 --> 01:42:29.241
Now!

973
01:42:43.672 --> 01:42:46.800
Commander. thank you.

974
01:43:34.139 --> 01:43:36.391
Mom's falling behind!

975
01:44:38.537 --> 01:44:39.704
Are you all right?

976
01:44:39.914 --> 01:44:41.081
You're safe now!

977
01:44:44.834 --> 01:44:45.835
Jane...

978
01:44:45.920 --> 01:44:46.921
Jane!

979
01:44:47.004 --> 01:44:49.965
Jane! We have to save my mom!

980
01:44:50.049 --> 01:44:51.383
I'm sorry. It's too late!

981
01:44:51.466 --> 01:44:52.676
We can't put you in danger.

982
01:44:52.759 --> 01:44:53.844
We must leave now!

983
01:44:53.928 --> 01:44:56.680
Please. help my mom!

984
01:44:57.389 --> 01:44:58.891
Please! Just this once!

985
01:44:59.058 --> 01:45:00.059
Go! Let's go!

986
01:45:00.350 --> 01:45:01.351
Let's go!

987
01:45:01.435 --> 01:45:02.602
You must wait!

988
01:45:05.314 --> 01:45:06.356
Please...

989
01:45:07.942 --> 01:45:09.902
Remain calm...

990
01:45:20.287 --> 01:45:21.663
Don't wait for me...

991
01:45:45.980 --> 01:45:46.981
No...

992
01:45:48.398 --> 01:45:49.399
Mom!

993
01:45:49.483 --> 01:45:52.277
Don't do it. Mom!

994
01:46:01.703 --> 01:46:02.746
Let go of me!

995
01:46:06.375 --> 01:46:07.376
Mom!

996
01:46:16.510 --> 01:46:18.137
Mom. please!

997
01:46:26.228 --> 01:46:29.023
She made a very sensible decision.

998
01:46:29.689 --> 01:46:33.568
It was for the best! For everyone...

999
01:46:34.694 --> 01:46:36.363
Sensible decision. my ass.

1000
01:46:38.407 --> 01:46:39.574
Did you even try?

1001
01:46:42.369 --> 01:46:43.370
Jung-seok...

1002
01:46:44.746 --> 01:46:46.248
You're tormented too!

1003
01:46:47.958 --> 01:46:49.293
You just gave up!

1004
01:46:49.376 --> 01:46:52.004
We have to save Mom!

1005
01:46:58.969 --> 01:47:00.554
I'll bring back your mom.

1006
01:47:01.763 --> 01:47:02.973
Wait right here.

1007
01:47:14.985 --> 01:47:17.196
Mom! Run!

1008
01:48:48.328 --> 01:48:50.705
- Mom!
- Mom!

1009
01:48:58.297 --> 01:48:59.298
Mom!

1010
01:50:16.291 --> 01:50:19.128
Don't worry. She'll be okay.

1011
01:50:23.883 --> 01:50:25.175
She'll be fine.

1012
01:50:39.023 --> 01:50:41.733
In a few hours. a new world will be waiting.

1013
01:50:43.527 --> 01:50:47.281
The world I knew wasn't bad either.

1014
01:51:20.652 --> 01:51:25.652
